    <text id="A6300T">
        <front id="d2">
            <div1 type="summary" id="d3">
                <p>Evans reassures Sibert of his love for her and discusses plans for an upcoming
                    visit.</p>
            </div1>
        </front>

        <body id="d4">
            <div1 type="letter" id="d5">
                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        <date value="1868-04-14">April 14 1868</date>
                        <name type="place">Staunton</name>
                    </dateline>
                    <salute>My Dear Mollie</salute>
                </opener>

                <p>Your dear &amp; welcome letter of the 9th came safely to hand I was truly
                    glad to <orig reg="hear">heare</orig> of your good health. I am Sorry you let
                    Such <orig reg="trifles">triffels</orig> make you So unhappy you must dismiss
                    from your mind what happened on my last visit. I love you my love may not show
                        <orig reg="itself">it's Self</orig>
                    <orig reg="always">allways</orig> on the Surface but deep down in the Chambers
                    of my heart I love you with all the devotion &amp; <orig reg="fervency"
                        >fervancey</orig> of my heart <pb n="2"/> Did you look for me last Saturday
                    if you did I hope you was not <orig reg="disappointed">disapointed</orig> for I
                    think I told you in my last letter it would be very <orig reg="doubtful"
                        >doughtful</orig>
                    <orig reg="about">a bout</orig> my coming though I would have come if I could
                    have gotten <orig reg="off">of</orig> from the Store You may look for Magnus
                    &amp; <orig reg="myself">my Self</orig> next Saturday for <orig
                        reg="certain">Surtian</orig> if nothing prevents us from coming which I hope
                    they will not we will Start <orig reg="very">verry</orig> Early in the morning
                    Magnus &amp; <orig reg="myself">my Self</orig> wants to take a general Fish
                    that is if McCue <pb n="3"/> will let us fish in his Run. I hope he will have no
                        <orig reg="objections">objecsions</orig> to us fishing. Your Pa <orig
                        reg="arrived">rived</orig> on yesterday he is quite well &amp; in fine
                        <orig reg="spirits">Spirets</orig> he will leave for home this Evening. I
                    Still love you the Same with all the true devotion of my heart &amp; Soul I
                    love you above all others in this world you are dearer <orig reg="than"
                    >then</orig> all others to me I love to be with you &amp; love to think of
                    you when absent from you. Ella &amp; <orig reg="family">familey</orig> are
                    all well give my love to your Ma Ham &amp; all the Children I love you more
                    &amp; more <orig reg="every">ever</orig> day of my life &amp; send a
                    loving Kiss to you God bless you good bye</p>

                <closer>
                    <salute>Yours</salute>
                    <signed>D H Evans</signed>
                </closer>
            </div1>
        </body>
    </text>
